0.99
, robust basally and tapering to terminus; dorsal caudal scales granular with six small tubercles on anterior tail whorls part; a single post-cloacal spur on each side of vent; subcaudals small, flat, imbricate, and smooth rounded, no enlarged median subcaudals (

Figure 
2

D).
